Chemstar Paint Industry Nigeria Limited, on Saturday, hosted its customers and distributors nationwide at an appreciation ceremony. According to the firm, the event held in Lagos, was organised to rewards its loyal customers and distributors. At the event was tagged, ‘Customers Forum,’ some of the firm’s distributors were rewarded with cash prizes and other gifts. The Group Managing Director of the firm, Mr Adedayo Paseda, said the 2020 and 2021 editions of the Customers Forum could not hold because of the COVID-19 pandemic. “In spite of the difficulties caused by the pandemic, many good things have happened in our lives and that of the company, hence, the need to thank God,” Paseda said. Also, the Chief Executive Officer of the firm, Dr Aderemi Awode, said the loyalty of the customers and distributors had kept the company going since its establishment in 1996. He said, “We have seen the need to celebrate our distributors who have been with us for the past 15 and 20 years. We are also celebrating our outstanding customers who have equally been our pillar of support between 1996 and 2020.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com